  "text": "Strains, plasmids and growth conditions All strains used are described in Table 1 . Vibrio fischeri ETJB1H was isolated from the light organ of Euprymna tasmanica from Jervis Bay, Australia [CITATION_1] . Strains were grown in either Luria-Bertani (LB; L À1 : 10 g tryptone, 5 g yeast extract and 10 g NaCl) or Luria-Bertani high Salt (LBS; L À1 : 10 g tryptone, 5 g yeast extract, 20 g NaCl, 50 mL 1 M Tris, pH 7.5, 3.75 mL 80% glycerol and 950 mL dH 2 O) media at 37 and 28°C. For selection of specific mutant strains, erythromycin (25 lg mL À1 ) was added to the media.",
